        "schemeImageUrl": "",
        "detailedDescription_md": "The Pradhan Mantri Matsya Sampada Yojana: Establishment of Medium RAS / Biofloc Culture System,  introduced by the Ministry Of Fisheries, Animal Husbandry &amp; Dairying, Government of India, aims to provide capital assistance to fish farmers and entrepreneurs for establishing medium-scale Recirculatory Aquaculture Systems (RAS) and Biofloc systems. These models promote high-density fish production in controlled environments, significantly reducing land and water usage. It is a centrally funded scheme with a 50:50 cost-sharing pattern between the Central and State Governments.\n\n- For RAS: Minimum 6 tanks of 30 m³ each (10 tons/crop)- For Biofloc: 25 tanks of 4 m diameter and 1 m height\n",
        "benefits_md": "\n- The project cost is ₹25,00,000/-\n\n> **** **Subsidy Distribution:**\n\n\n1. 40% subsidy for General Category beneficiaries.\n1. 60% subsidy for SC and Women category beneficiaries.\n\n",
        "briefDescription": "The scheme provides capital assistance to fish farmers and entrepreneurs for establishing medium-scale Recirculatory Aquaculture Systems (RAS) and Biofloc systems.",
        "exclusions_md": "<br>\n\n",
