      "schemeDefinitions": [],
      "eligibilityCriteria": {
        "eligibilityDescription_md": "\n1. The applicant must be a permanent resident of Haryana and possess a valid Parivar Pehchan Patra (PPP).\n1. The applicant must have access to own land or hold a registered lease for a minimum period of 10 years.\n1. The applicant must ensure that the land is free from any legal and financial encumbrances.\n1. The applicant must have access to a reliable water source such as a canal, tube well, river, or similar.\n1. The applicant must provide a valid training certificate in fisheries or aquaculture.\n1. The applicant must agree to manage and maintain the system at their own cost after setup.\n1. The applicant must submit a Detailed Project Report (DPR) or a Self-Contained Proposal (SCP).\n1. The applicant must sign an agreement with the Department of Fisheries to avail benefits under the scheme.\n\n",
